The Senate, Wednesday, issued a stern warning to the Federal Inland Revenue Service (FRSC), the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) and other Ministries, Departments and agencies of the Federal government for failing to submit their audited accounts to the Senate in order for the Legislature perform its oversight responsibility.  Chairman of the Senate Committee on Public Accounts, Senator Matthew Urhoghide speaking at a press conference in Abuja revealed that the Apex bank and other strategic agencies of government have turned down the demand for submission of reports on their expenditure activities from 2017 â€“ 2019.  Senator Urhoghide noted that the situation has frustrated the efforts of the 9th Senate, while corruption and mass fraud were recurrent decimal in the affected government establishments.  Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that the lawmaker while issuing a seven-day deadline to submit their reports, it ordered that, no agency of government would be spared on how financial transactions were handled within the ambit of laws that established the particular agency.